vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 6
  }
}
title: |md
  ## FSM: Block Comment `/* … */` Detection
  `_scan_block_comment()` — called after `/*` consumed
  **Non-nesting guarantee:** no counter, no stack — two-state lookahead only
| {near: top-center}
# ── States ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
initial: "" {
  shape: circle
  width: 24
  style: {
    fill: "#1a1a1a"
    stroke: "#1a1a1a"
  }
}
SCANNING: "SCANNING\n──────────────────\ninv: inside comment body\ncursor: any non-'*' char\naction: advance() → discards char\n         advance() handles '\\n'\n         → line++ column=1" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#4B3F8A"
    font-color: white
    bold: true
    border-radius: 8
    stroke: "#7B6AC0"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}
SAW_STAR: "SAW_STAR\n──────────────────\ninv: last consumed char was '*'\ncursor: peeking next char\naction: waiting to see if\n         next char is '/'" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#2E6B9E"
    font-color: white
    bold: true
    border-radius: 8
    stroke: "#5BA3D4"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}
CLOSED: "CLOSED\n──────────────────\ninv: consumed '*' then '/'\noutput: NO TOKEN emitted\naction: return immediately\n         (success path)" {
  shape: oval
  style: {
    fill: "#2A7A3B"
    font-color: white
    bold: true
    stroke: "#4DC462"
    stroke-width: 3
    double-border: true
  }
}
EOF_ERROR: "EOF_ERROR\n──────────────────\ninv: is_at_end() in any state\noutput: ERROR token emitted\n  lexeme = source[start:current]\n  line   = token_start_line\n  col    = token_start_column\naction: append ERROR, return" {
  shape: oval
  style: {
    fill: "#8B1A1A"
    font-color: white
    bold: true
    stroke: "#E05252"
    stroke-width: 3
  }
}
# ── Entry arrow ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
initial -> SCANNING: "entry\n(after '/*' consumed)" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#CCCCCC"
    font-color: "#CCCCCC"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}
# ── Transitions ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SCANNING -> SAW_STAR: "peek() == '*'\nthen advance()" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#5BA3D4"
    font-color: "#5BA3D4"
    stroke-width: 2
    bold: true
  }
}
SCANNING -> SCANNING: "peek() != '*' AND != EOF\nadvance() → discard char\n(if char == '\\n': line++, col=1\n else: col++)" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#9B89D4"
    font-color: "#9B89D4"
    stroke-width: 1
    stroke-dash: 3
  }
}
SAW_STAR -> CLOSED: "peek() == '/'\nthen advance()\n→ return (no token)" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#4DC462"
    font-color: "#4DC462"
    stroke-width: 3
    bold: true
  }
}
SAW_STAR -> SAW_STAR: "peek() == '*'\nthen advance()\n(stay: another '*'\n may precede '/')" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#5BA3D4"
    font-color: "#5BA3D4"
    stroke-width: 2
    stroke-dash: 4
  }
}
SAW_STAR -> SCANNING: "peek() != '/' AND != '*' AND != EOF\nadvance() → discard char\n(the '*' was literal; resume)" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#9B89D4"
    font-color: "#9B89D4"
    stroke-width: 1
    stroke-dash: 3
  }
}
SCANNING -> EOF_ERROR: "is_at_end()\n→ append ERROR\n   at '/*' position" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#E05252"
    font-color: "#E05252"
    stroke-width: 2
    bold: true
    stroke-dash: 5
  }
}
SAW_STAR -> EOF_ERROR: "is_at_end()\n(no '/' after '*')\n→ append ERROR\n   at '/*' position" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#E05252"
    font-color: "#E05252"
    stroke-width: 2
    bold: true
    stroke-dash: 5
  }
}
# ── Annotation boxes ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
non_nesting_note: |md
  **Non-Nesting Guarantee**
  No depth counter. No stack.
  The DFA has exactly **2 live states**.
  The first `*/` encountered — regardless
  of any `/*` inside — closes the comment.
  `/* outer /* inner */ rest */`
  closes at the first `*/` after `inner`.
  `rest */` enters NORMAL mode.
| {
  near: bottom-left
  style: {
    fill: "#2A2A3A"
    font-color: "#C8C0F0"
    stroke: "#7B6AC0"
    border-radius: 6
  }
}
pathological_note: |md
  **Edge Case: `/***/`**
  1. `/*` consumed → enter SCANNING
  2. peek `*` → advance → SAW_STAR
  3. peek `*` (≠ `/`) → advance → SAW_STAR (self-loop)
  4. peek `/` → advance → **CLOSED** ✓
  The SAW_STAR → SAW_STAR self-loop on `*`
  is the key that handles `***/`, `****/`, etc.
| {
  near: bottom-right
  style: {
    fill: "#1A2A2A"
    font-color: "#88DCF7"
    stroke: "#5BA3D4"
    border-radius: 6
  }
}
advance_note: |md
  **`advance()` invariant**
  Every character consumed via `advance()`.
  `\n` inside comment → `line++`, `col=1`.
  Position tracking is **free** — no extra
  logic needed in `_scan_block_comment()`.
  Token after comment has correct line/col.
| {
  near: top-right
  style: {
    fill: "#1A2A1A"
    font-color: "#9BE89B"
    stroke: "#4DC462"
    border-radius: 6
  }
}